quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The All-Merciful
  55,2,He taught the Qur'an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,"He has taught him distinct (Literally: evident (demonstration) (speech)"
  55,5,The sun and the moon (run) to all-precisely reckoned (courses)
  55,6,And the star and the trees prostrate themselves
  55,7,"And the heaven, He raised it up, and laid down the Balance"
  55,8,That you should not be inordinate in the Balance
  55,9,"And keep up the weight with equity, and do not cause loss in the Balance"
  55,10,"And the earth, He laid down for (all) beings"
  55,11,"Therein are fruits, and palm-trees comprising sheaths"
  55,12,"And grains owning the blades, (Or: husks) and all-fragrant herbs. (Or: soothing comfort)"
  55,13,"Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) (i.e., the jinn and mankind) cry lies"
  55,14,He created man of dry clay like earthenware
  55,15,And He created the jinn (race) of a merging of fire
  55,16,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,17,The Lord of the two easts and The Lord of the two wests
  55,18,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,19,He merged the two seas (that) meet together
  55,20,"Between them (both) is an isthmus (i.e., an obstruction) (which) they do not overpass. (Literally: none of them is inequitable)"
  55,21,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,22,"From (both of) them come out (Literally: go out) the pearl and all-merged coral (stones)"
  55,23,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies
  55,24,"And to Him belong the running (ships), (sailing) aloft (Literally: raised up, erected) in the sea like landmarks"
  55,25,Then to whichever of your Lord's boons do you (both) cry lies